narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: There were some enjoyable and lively talks.
I learned a lot. The breadth of interests of different speakers was also good. Definitely liked having less neuroscience oriented faculty like Jiaying or Todd, for instance.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Strengths: Good range of speakers Lively discussion Weaknesses: The room is awful: there are not enough chairs most of the time and the projector needs a new bulb There should be more student speakers (during the off weeks, don't reduce the amount of external speakers)
I'm not sure I like the 4-5:50pm time, but I know that for some faculty, it certainly is better--and I learn a lot just from hearing their questions, so maybe 4-5:50pm might still be better.
